          <div class="order-2 md:order-1">
            <MarketingScreenshot
              src="/images/marketing/dvsa-progress-tracking.webp"
              width={1440}
              height={900}
              alt="DVSA competency tracking grid showing 8 skill categories with proficiency levels from Not Started to Reflection"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="order-1 md:order-2">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-3">DVSA Progress Tracking</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Full DVSA competency framework — 8 categories, 27 skills with 6-level proficiency scale. Cross-instructor continuity so any instructor sees the full picture.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Student Portal -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 items-center mb-16">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-3">Student Portal <span class="badge-coming-soon ml-2">Coming Soon</span></h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Secure student login to view lessons, track DVSA progress, check package balances, and manage personal details.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-center">
            <MarketingScreenshot
              src="/images/marketing/portal-dashboard-mobile.webp"
              width={375}
              height={1193}
              alt="Student self-service portal on mobile showing upcoming lesson, progress summary, and active packages"
              mobile
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Invoicing & Packages -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 items-center mb-16">
          <div class="order-2 md:order-1">
            <MarketingScreenshot
              src="/images/marketing/payments.webp"
              width={1440}
              height={900}
              alt="Professional invoice with itemised charges, VAT breakdown, and email delivery status"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="order-1 md:order-2">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-3">Invoicing & Packages</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Invoices with line items, payment recording (cash, bank transfer, cheque), and email delivery. Lesson packages with automatic hour tracking.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Feature blocks without dedicated screenshots — clean card grid -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-100">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-3">Online Booking Widget <span class="badge-coming-soon ml-2">Coming Soon</span></h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Let new students book lessons from your website — 24/7, without a phone call. Embed the DriveSchoolPro booking widget on any website with a single code snippet. Students choose their lesson type, pick an available time slot, enter their details, and book instantly. You control which times are available, which lesson types are bookable, and how far ahead students can book. Existing students can also book directly through their secure portal.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-100">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-3">Lesson Delivery Workflow</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">After each lesson, record exactly what happened — directly from your phone. The outcome wizard walks you through selecting which DVSA competencies were covered, updating proficiency levels, and adding instructor notes. Everything is saved to the student's progress record instantly, so the next instructor (or you, next week) knows exactly where to pick up. Students will soon see their updated progress through their self-service portal.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-100">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-3">Driving Test Management</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Track practical test bookings with date, test centre, and test type. When results come in, record pass or fail with examiner notes. The dashboard shows upcoming tests across all students, and you can monitor your school's first-time pass rate to measure the quality of your instruction over time.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-100">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-3">Student Documents &amp; Compliance</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Upload and track student documents — provisional licence, passport photos, medical declarations — with expiry date alerts. The dashboard flags documents approaching expiry so nothing slips through the cracks. Custom document categories let you track whatever your school requires.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto prose prose-lg mt-16">

        <h2 id="types" class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-6">Types of Driving School Software</h2>

        <p>Not every product sold as "driving school software" does the same job. Broadly, what's on the market falls into four types, and knowing which you're looking at saves a lot of wasted trials.</p>

        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li><strong>All-in-one management platforms:</strong> The most complete option — scheduling, DVSA progress tracking, invoicing, test management, and reporting in one system. DriveSchoolPro sits here. Best for ADIs and schools that want a single source of truth rather than several tools bolted together.</li>
          <li><strong>Scheduling-only tools:</strong> Focused on the calendar — booking lessons, avoiding clashes, and sending reminders. Useful if scheduling is your only pain point, but they rarely track pupil progress or handle payments, so you end up running a spreadsheet alongside.</li>
          <li><strong>Generic booking and calendar apps:</strong> Off-the-shelf appointment tools adapted for lessons. They're cheap and familiar, but they don't understand the three-way clash of student, instructor, and vehicle, and they have no concept of the DVSA framework.</li>
          <li><strong>Free or spreadsheet-based systems:</strong> A paper diary, a shared spreadsheet, or a free tier of a generic app. Fine when you have a handful of pupils, but they break down as you grow and offer no automation. See our guide to <a href="/free-driving-school-software/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline">free driving school software</a> for an honest look at the limits.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>DriveSchoolPro is a purpose-built all-in-one platform for UK ADIs — so you get the depth of a management system without stitching several products together. Compare it directly in our <a href="/driving-school-scheduling-software/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline">scheduling software</a> and <a href="/driving-school-management-software/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline">management software</a> guides.</p>

        <h2 id="cost" class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-12 mb-6">How Much Does Driving School Software Cost?</h2>

        <p>UK driving school software ranges from free (limited tools and spreadsheets) to £100+ a month for enterprise platforms with per-user fees. DriveSchoolPro keeps pricing simple and transparent, with every feature included and no charge per student:</p>

        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li><strong>Solo Plan — £22/month:</strong> For independent ADIs. Unlimited students, the full DVSA 27-skills framework, scheduling with conflict detection, automated reminders, and invoicing — everything a solo instructor needs to run professionally.</li>
          <li><strong>School Plan — £22/month for your first instructor, then £12/month per additional instructor (up to 5):</strong> Adds multi-instructor calendars, vehicle fleet and compliance tracking, business analytics, and role-based access. A 3-instructor school is £46/month; a 5-instructor school is £70/month, or £14 per instructor.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>There are no setup fees, no per-lesson charges, and no long-term contract — plans are month-to-month. Every plan starts with a {OFFER.short}, no credit card required. At £22/month the Solo Plan pays for itself the moment it saves you an hour of admin, and most ADIs report saving 10+ hours a week. See the <a href="/pricing/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline">full pricing breakdown</a> for cost-per-student figures and FAQs.</p>

        <h2 id="how-to-choose" class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-12 mb-6">How to Choose Driving School Software</h2>

        <p>The right driving school software is the one your whole business will actually use day to day. When you're weighing up options — DriveSchoolPro included — test each one against the things that matter most to a UK ADI:</p>

        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li><strong>DVSA progress tracking:</strong> Can it record each pupil against the official 27 skills, not just store free-text notes? Structured tracking is what gives you cross-instructor continuity and reliable test-readiness.</li>
          <li><strong>True three-way scheduling:</strong> Does it check student, instructor, and vehicle availability together before allowing a booking? Anything less still lets double-bookings slip through.</li>
          <li><strong>Mobile-first for instructors:</strong> You'll use it between lessons, at the kerbside, on a phone. If the mobile experience is just a shrunken desktop screen, it won't get used.</li>
          <li><strong>Transparent, predictable pricing:</strong> Watch for per-student fees, per-SMS charges, and tiers that punish growth. Know your real monthly cost before you commit.</li>
          <li><strong>A genuine free trial:</strong> You should be able to run real lessons, real pupils, and real invoices during a trial — not just click around a demo. DriveSchoolPro offers a {OFFER.short} with full access.</li>
          <li><strong>UK and DVSA focus:</strong> Generic international tools rarely model the UK test, ADI roles, or compliance. Software built for UK driving schools fits the way you already work.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>For a side-by-side view, read our <a href="/blog/best-driving-school-software/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline">best driving school software comparison</a> and the head-to-head <a href="/compare/total-drive/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline">DriveSchoolPro vs Total Drive</a>.</p>

      </div>
    </div>
